<p>Given a string containing just the characters <code>'('</code> and
    <code>')'</code>, find the length of the longest
    valid (well-formed) parentheses substring.
</p>
<p> For <code>"(()"</code>,
    the longest valid parentheses substring is <code>"()"</code>, which has
    length = 2.
</p>
<p> Another example is <code>")()())"</code>, where the
    longest valid parentheses substring is <code>"()()"</code>,
    which has length = 4.
</p>
